    "Background": {
      "text": "Abbreviation: PSGN\nMost common cause of acute nephritis worldwide\nRisk greatest in children 5-12 years old and adults >60\nCaused by glomerular immune complex disease induced by specific nephritogenic strains of group A beta-hemolytic streptococcus (GAS)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Varies from asymptomatic to microscopic\nhematuria\nto acute nephritic syndrome (gross hematuria,\nproteinuria\n, edema,\nhypertension\n, and\nacute kidney injury\n)\nMost common features:\nEdema\nGross\nhematuria\nHypertension\nHistory of recent\nstrep\ninfection (e.g.\nstrep pharyngitis\n,\nimpetigo\n)",
